    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-04T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="737"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/195: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-04T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 4, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 4—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. My telegram No. 5, November 6, 4 p.m., from Ankara. I have just received from
                    the Turkish Minister for Foreign Affairs a note proposing the negotiation of an
                    arrangement for reciprocal tariff reductions. I am acknowledging it in
                    accordance with your telegram No. 1, November 19, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
